        <type>void *</type>
        <definition>void* lely_compat_memcpy</definition>
        <argsstring>(void *s1, const void *s2, size_t n)</argsstring>
        <name>lely_compat_memcpy</name>
        <param>
          <type>void *</type>
          <declname>s1</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>const void *</type>
          <declname>s2</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>size_t</type>
          <declname>n</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Copies <bold>n</bold> bytes from the object pointed to by <bold>s2</bold> into the object pointed to by <bold>s1</bold>. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>If copying takes place between objects that overlap, the behavior is undefined.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="return"><para><bold>s1</bold>. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="lib/compat/string.c" line="29" column="1" bodyfile="lib/compat/string.c" bodystart="29" bodyend="36"/>
      </memberdef>
      <memberdef kind="function" id="string_8c_1a8368d138c27fbd8f6c7d939c7f13f14d" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void *</type>
        <definition>void* lely_compat_memmove</definition>
        <argsstring>(void *s1, const void *s2, size_t n)</argsstring>
        <name>lely_compat_memmove</name>
        <param>
          <type>void *</type>
          <declname>s1</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>const void *</type>
          <declname>s2</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>size_t</type>
          <declname>n</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Copies <bold>n</bold> bytes from the object pointed to by <bold>s2</bold> into the object pointed to by <bold>s1</bold>. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Copying takes place as if the <bold>n</bold> bytes from the object pointed to by <bold>s2</bold> are first copied into a temporary array of <bold>n</bold> bytes that does not overlap the objects pointed to by <bold>s1</bold> and <bold>s2</bold>, and then the <bold>n</bold> bytes from the temporary array are copied into the object pointed to by <bold>s1</bold>.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="return"><para><bold>s1</bold>. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="lib/compat/string.c" line="39" column="1" bodyfile="lib/compat/string.c" bodystart="39" bodyend="53"/>
      </memberdef>
      <memberdef kind="function" id="string_8c_1a17cdb2eb194469f3a32d7d581fabbd18" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int lely_compat_memcmp</definition>
        <argsstring>(const void *s1, const void *s2, size_t n)</argsstring>
        <name>lely_compat_memcmp</name>
        <param>
          <type>const void *</type>
          <declname>s1</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>const void *</type>
          <declname>s2</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>size_t</type>
          <declname>n</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Compares the first <bold>n</bold> bytes (each interpreted as an <computeroutput>unsigned char</computeroutput>) of the object pointed to by <bold>s1</bold> to the first <bold>n</bold> btyes of the object pointed to by <bold>s2</bold>. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The sign of a non-zero return value shall be determined by the sign of the difference between the values of the first pair of bytes (both interpreted as type <computeroutput>unsigned char</computeroutput>) that differ in the objects being compared.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="return"><para>an integer greater than, equal to, or less than 0, if the object pointed to by <bold>s1</bold> is greater than, equal to, or less than the object pointed to by <bold>s2</bold>. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="lib/compat/string.c" line="56" column="1" bodyfile="lib/compat/string.c" bodystart="56" bodyend="65"/>
      </memberdef>
      <memberdef kind="function" id="string_8c_1aef65e445168dcd83788d6a5c0ce769ae" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int lely_compat_strcmp</definition>
        <argsstring>(const char *s1, const char *s2)</argsstring>
        <name>lely_compat_strcmp</name>
        <param>
          <type>const char *</type>
          <declname>s1</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>const char *</type>
          <declname>s2</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Compares the string pointed to by <bold>s1</bold> to the string pointed to by <bold>s2</bold>. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The sign of a non-zero return value shall be determined by the sign of the difference between the values of the first pair of bytes (both interpreted as type <computeroutput>unsigned char</computeroutput>) that differ in the strings being compared.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="return"><para>an integer greater than, equal to, or less than 0, if the string pointed to by <bold>s1</bold> is greater than, equal to, or less than the string pointed to by <bold>s2</bold>. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="lib/compat/string.c" line="68" column="1" bodyfile="lib/compat/string.c" bodystart="68" bodyend="78"/>
